      • isEnabled

        public boolean isEnabled()
        Description copied from interface: com.sun.javafx.scene.web.Debugger
        Determines whether the debugger is enabled. A debugger's Debugger.sendMessage(java.lang.String) method may only be called while the debugger is enabled. The message callback object registered with a debugger is only called while the debugger is enabled.
        Specified by:
        isEnabled in interface com.sun.javafx.scene.web.Debugger
        Returns:
        true if the debugger is enabled, false otherwise.

      • setEnabled

        public void setEnabled(boolean enabled)
        Description copied from interface: com.sun.javafx.scene.web.Debugger
        Enables or disables the debugger. A debugger's Debugger.sendMessage(java.lang.String) method may only be called while the debugger is enabled. The message callback object registered with a debugger is only called while the debugger is enabled.

        This method has no effect if the enabled parameter is true and the debugger is already enabled, or if the enabled parameter is false and the debugger is already disabled.

        Specified by:
        setEnabled in interface com.sun.javafx.scene.web.Debugger
        Parameters:
        enabled - specifies whether the debugger should be enabled or disabled.

      • sendMessage

        public void sendMessage(java.lang.String message)
        Description copied from interface: com.sun.javafx.scene.web.Debugger
        Sends a message to the debugger. The message is a text string in the format specified by the WebKit Remote Debugging Protocol.

        This method may only be called while the debugger is enabled.

        Specified by:
        sendMessage in interface com.sun.javafx.scene.web.Debugger
        Parameters:
        message - the message to be sent to the debugger. May not be null.

      • getMessageCallback

        public Callback<java.lang.String,java.lang.Void> getMessageCallback()
        Description copied from interface: com.sun.javafx.scene.web.Debugger
        Returns the message callback object registered with the debugger. The debugger calls the message callback object's Callback.call(P) method to deliver a message to the debugger frontend. The message passed to the message callback is a text string in the format specified by the WebKit Remote Debugging Protocol.
        Specified by:
        getMessageCallback in interface com.sun.javafx.scene.web.Debugger
        Returns:
        the message callback object registered with the debugger, or null if there is no such object.

      • setMessageCallback

        public void setMessageCallback(Callback<java.lang.String,java.lang.Void> callback)
        Description copied from interface: com.sun.javafx.scene.web.Debugger
        Registers a message callback object with the debugger. The debugger calls the message callback object's Callback.call(P) method to deliver a message to the debugger frontend. The message passed to the message callback is a text string in the format specified by the WebKit Remote Debugging Protocol.
        Specified by:
        setMessageCallback in interface com.sun.javafx.scene.web.Debugger
        Parameters:
        callback - the message callback object to be registered with the debugger. May be null.
